ike you did with the snow man . She really pops out of the card <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=triclone>Triclone</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://liquid2k.com/triclone/misc/button.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/8/02 8:14:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8094.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://liquid2k.com/triclone/misc/avatar.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Season's greetings in brilliant color!</span><hr size=1> Awesome <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ! the snow effect is just uncanny.  Not much beef here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
My comment is only for her hair which, similarly to Dark comment about the clothes, are too neon-y bright in that setting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jspuonti>JSPuonti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>In Brilliant Color <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/jspicon.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/8/02 10:12:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8094.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Good points all around</span><hr size=1> Thank you for your feedback, everyone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
There is a good reason for the absurdly bright colors on the girl, though: originally I colored her like this, and then added a color layer above it all that made the girl look more like she was part of the picture (you know, yellow'ish highlights from the streetlight above, blue'ish shadows on her clothing, etc). It looked very &quot;realistic&quot; shading-wise, but it was rather depressing. Well, maybe not depressing, but different <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I got to thinking that hey, this is a Christmas card and it's supposed to be happy and bright, so I got rid of the &quot;realistic&quot; coloring and kept her colors bright. What you see was therefore done out of personal choice, although I can understand why it might seem too saturated <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Thanks again!<br>
